ed by analysing the vdW contributions. In all\niodide-based hybrid perovskites the interaction between the organic cation and\nthe iodide anions provides the largest lattice-constant change, followed by\niodine-iodine and the organic cation - heavy-metal cation interaction. These\ncorrections follow an almost linear dependence on the lattice constant within\nthe range considered in our study, and are therefore approximately additive.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 29 Feb 2016 12:29:29 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 12 Mar 2016 00:34:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-03"}
